track_notes:
This summit is located on property belonging to The Nature Conservancy, Davis Mountains Preserve. They allow public access to the summit only on specific days and weekends during the year. 

http://www.nature.org/ourinitiatives/regions/northamerica/unitedstates/texas/placesweprotect/davis-mountains-preserve.xml

From I-10 at Kent, Texas, head south on TX Hwy 118.  At 23 miles, pass the junction of Hwy 166, continue 5 more miles south on 118 to Madrea Canyon Road at the gate to the Conservancy.  Enter and proceed to the HQ building for registration.

Obtain a map from the HQ building before departing.  The roads to the trailhead require a high-clearance vehicle.

The trail begins beyond the gate at the end of the road. the trail curves to the left and climbs into the forest area.  When you reach Bridge Gap you stay to the right, following the main trail.  At the final ascent you go around the right side of the bald knob and look for a path through the trees on the left.
